<br>
In my experience a 39 focused fire pet does well here, with some nuking help from you.  By the time you get your 44 fire pet, he should basically eat them.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FULL DWARF KILLING GUIDE - Rhiannan, Povar</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>INTRO</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
First of all, you should know that I did this starting at level 29 and I'm sharing what I know because I just hit 47 and can no longer stand Butcherblock so the rest of you are no longer competing with me for dorf spawns. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>TARGETS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Casters have various options for targets. This is written by a druid for druids which means some of this part may not apply to other classes that can be evil races. If you're an evil race and don't care about faction, kill every dorf in sight. <br>
<br>
In my experience, the resistances and factions of the guards here are not worth the experience they give. I never killed them, why bother when their faction can make killing the primary targets easier. Note that guards do not blink an eye if you kill the KaladimCitizen faction dorfs in front of them as long as you aren't already KOS by the guards. <br>
<br>
You will also find several dorfs holding fishing poles. These are the same level and hit points as the non-fishers, but have a much more nasty faction hit. Merchants and guards will both think less of you after you kill a fisherman. If you're not a druid and don't care about this faction hit, these dorfs are good targets because the rest of us just leave them alone. There's one south of the docks near Den (Ironblen) and one at the base of each dock. <br>
<br>
The primary target for druids are all KaladimCitzen faction and located: <br>
<br>
North of crossroads (Delin*). <br>
South of the docks near druid circle (Den*). <br>
South of the docks inside hut near Den (Lann, Dalbar). <br>
On each of the actual docks (Magnus, Glorin). <br>
In two of the huts inside the dock area (Gann, Doran). <br>
Stone circle just outside the dock area to the east (Darm, Ganbar). <br>
Just outside of Kaladim to the east (Alun, Gibi). <br>
Near chessboard (Signus). <br>
South of bandit camp (Signus). <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>RESPAWN</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
As you can see, there's a good selection here. The two marked with an asterisk above respawn much faster than the rest (6 minutes I believe). The others respawn twice as slow. As you can probably guess, the single spawns that don't respawn fast aren't very good but they can be used to pass the time waiting for a better spot or the one near the bandit camp makes a nice supplement to Den's House, Delin, or Stone Circle. <br>
<br>
Don't be fooled by spawn times though. In fact, try to be courteous and not take spawns that you can't keep up with. For example, if you have Den or Delin and it takes all your mana and then you spend 10 minutes meditating, why not trade with somebody who can keep up and kill her as soon as she respawns?  In that situation, any of the double spawns will accomplish the same thing for you and you may make a friend in the process. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CAMPS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
The above list is grouped by logical &quot;camps.&quot; Some camps are closer to each other than others. For example, Den, Lann, and Dalbar are all in the same spot. But you can pull both camps off to their respective sides and not aggro the other camp.  Some camps can also be used to supplement others.  The Stone Circle can be used to supplement the Dock Huts if you can't get all the spawns at the docks to yourself. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>MONEY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Every dorf listed drops a 2-handed axe. Even though Verant recently nerfed the price that merchants buy the axes from 20-21pp down to 3-4pp, the money is still not bad. Along with the guaranteed axes, the dorfs occassionally drop 1-5pp in coin, fine steel weapons, small ringmail pieces, various words and runes. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>LOCATION</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Certain camps are better than others based on location. Den is very close to the druid circle merchant. In addition, there is usually somebody else camping other dorfs at that spot who will sit and chat with you (and vouch for your spot while you sell). Delin on the other hand is a fast respawn but there aren't any merchants nearby. You will make a lot of trips to sell so keep this in mind. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>STARTING</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
When you are level 29-34ish, you will need a partner. Avoid grouping with other druids unless you have no other choices. Grouping with enchanters is great because of clarity. Other spells casters are decent here too, especially pet classes, but melee types are basically useless due to how hard the dorfs hit and the fact that it's difficult to keep the dorf from turning on them. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>KITING</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
I've tried the other strategies like root/DoT but for numerous reason I am convinced that snare/DD is the best way to do it. By 29 you should be pretty good at this tactic already so I won't go into it much here. All dorfs on the list are level 35 and have about 1675 hit points. <br>
<br>
Keep both combust and lightning memorized. Early in your career, lightning will get resisted slightly less often. When you start to solo around 35, use combust until the target is almost dead then if you think lightning (99 damage) is enough to finish, use that to save some mana. Once you get firestrike, use that primarily but keep both of the other two DD spells memorized. After your firestrike caps (302 damage) with no resists and the dorf not stopping to regen hit points near the end, it takes exactly 5 firestrikes and 1 combust to do the job. After awhile, you'll get used to how to compensate for partial resists midfight to kill them as efficiently as possible. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>HARMONY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
There are a few double spawns that require harmony to pull one at a time. Be sure to cast harmony at least twice if not three times on one of the two, then pull the other one with snare. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>INVISIBILITY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Some of the spawn pairs are inside huts. To pull them, use camo before opening the door. Open the door while invis to target one. Move to a safe distance, cast harmony two or three times, reinvis yourself, open the door and target the other. Then use snare to pull the one that you didn't harmonize. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FACTION</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
If you follow these guidelines, your only faction hit will be with KaladimCitizen. I have been in most places of Kaladim and I'm yet to bump into a single resident that I'm KOS to. My faction with the merchants is great and killing the dorfs has only affected my faction with the actual dorfs I've listed as targets. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EXPERIENCE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
This place is extremely good experience once you get a good camp and get into a rhythm. Even at 46 it was much faster than any group I've been in so far (including bats/bugs in SolB and King Room in LGuk). Once you've had a good camp here, you'll find it difficult to put up with the slower experience and much higher risk of death in dungeons. But be careful not to spend too much time here, knowing the dungeons can be very helpful later on when you hit 47 or 48 and find the dorfs are no longer a viable source of experience. <br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
